The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Now, Spurs fans clash with police in Sevilla 

Madrid/Rome: Even if Italian security officials defended the conduct of police in Wednesdays clashes with Manchester United fans in Rome, fresh violence erupted in Sevilla on Thursday. 

A number of Tottenham Hotspur fans were injured after clashing with Spanish riot police during the first half of their sides Uefa Cup quarter-final, first leg. 

Faustino Valdes, the Madrid governments representative in Seville, said Friday: Some Tottenham fans under the influence of alcohol attacked the private security officers and police... and we also have arrested some (seven) Tottenham fans who should be now appearing in court. 

Meanwhile the Italy governments top security official in Rome, prefect Achille Serra, called a news conference to show several video clips from the Champions League match against AS Roma, in which he said it was clear the Uniteds fans started the clashes. 

A penalty from Frederic Kanoute and an Alexander Kherzhakov header gave holders Sevilla a 2-1 first-leg lead over Tottenham. Osasuna and Espanyol also established first-leg leads. (Agencies) 




